funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide Technical Assistance and Trainings to water operators, utility managers, and/or council members in Fairbanks or in a surrounding road service community and two onsite village visits to facilitate the Workshop in a Box: Sustainable Management of Rural and Small Systems. The project will provide five classroom trainings to approximately 60-75 water operators, utility managers, and/or council members (based on 12-15 participants per class) in low-income rural interior villages and other Alaskan communities by utilizing partnerships within the State of Alaska and two on-site village visits to facilitate the Workshop in a Box; Sustainable Management of Rural and Small Systems Workshops for utility managers and council members. These workshops are centered on a self-assessment technique and end with a community-driven plan to improve performance in one of ten key management areas. A focus on Best Practices Scores will also increase competitiveness for funding.

funding_code: ELECTRIC FFB - OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to finance generation system upgrades and modification projects for the Green Lake 16.5 MW hydroelectric facility. CBS is an Alaskan city and borough located on Baranof Island and on the southern half of Chichagof Island situated in southeast Alaska. The population of Sitka is roughly 8,700 residents, served by approximately 5,539 electric meters. It is currently the tenth largest city by population in Alaska and, in terms of area, it is largest in the state with an incorporated area of about 2,870 square miles.

borrower_name: Byte Networking LLC dba Fibre Alaska
funding_code: COMMUNITY CONNECTIVITY-ORIENTED GTS
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a 4.7 mile Fiber-to-the Premises system to benefit430 residents and 16 businesses in the Gustavus, Hoonah-Angoon County, Alaska service area.The existing microwave link providing backhaul to the town will be upgraded. Subscribers will have access to service up to packages up to 50 Mbps down and 10 Mbps up, expanding access to economic, educational, health care, and public safety opportunities. A community center will be provided in an existing building where residents can access the Internet free of charge for at least two years.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help fund the Kashunamiut School District distance learning project. The project will serve Chevak Village, an extremely remote Alaskan village of 938 people, most of whom are Cupik Alaska Natives. The grant will connect the students, faculty, and staff of Chevak School with each other, their classrooms, and outside resources. The results will minimize disruptions to education, increase collaboration, and expand educational, professional, and vocational options. This is a Title One school serving pre-k through 12th grade.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide distance learning opportunities to several students located in the Lake and Peninsula School District. The total population that will benefit is 1,550. This project will be able to provide educational programs to students and teachers who are located in rural areas.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Lower Kuskokwim School District install new video conferencing equipment to support K-12 students with a focus on science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) courses, as well as student activities, such as the Spelling Bee and Battle of the Books. Moreover, Project Achieve also will allow for the continuous teaching of tribal languages, traditions and customs; the use of the equipment for Parent Advisory Committees, local School Board meetings and trainings; and will provide teachers with the necessary resources to attend in-service webinars on specific subjects and provide necessary training, Due to COVID-19, the district expanded distance learning to all grades, prior to the pandemic distance learning technology was reserved for students in the higher grades (seven-12). Increased technology will assist LKSD in meeting all the needs of the students, allowing for the creation of a blended learning environment where education may be done in-person or via distance learning if the need arises. The total population that will utilize the technology will be approximately 4,000 students, teachers, staff and family members in the Bethel Census Area.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to increase access to virtual instruction, specifically science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) courses, as well as career and technical education courses, including simulation. Through Project Ignite, the North Slope Borough School District will use videoconferencing technology, which will allow increased student and staff interactions, such as trainings, in-services, and labs. Project Ignite will also allow the North Slope Borough School District to implement two learning labs at rural sites. These labs will create and share real-time content, classes, and activities. Project Ignite will help provide the school districts extremely rural villages access to additional education resources and allow for continuous teaching of tribal languages, traditions, and customs. More than 2,000 residents are expected to benefit from this project.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to connect five end-user sites in the Nome Census Area, Bethel Census Area, Northwest Artic Borough, Dillingham Census Area and Southeast Fairbanks Census Area to two hub sites at the University of Alaska-Fairbanks. The project will enable students in remote locations to join classes around the state through any web conferencing platform connected to classroom PCs. Each computer will have a touch screen display at the lectern that will be mirrored on a projector or TV at the front of the classroom.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide a septic tank, effluent pump, and pressure mounded drain field to six homes in False Pass, Alaska. The septic tank will be installed to capture solids, followed by an effluent pump that will transfer effluent into a mounded drain field. Assuming the worst-case condition that seasonal high groundwater reaches the existing grade, a four-foot sand layer will be installed above grade to ensure the required groundwater separation distance is met. The wastewater will be discharged at the top of the sand filter layer. The drain field will be capped and sloped to grade.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deliver a series of solid waste management trainings and provide direct assistance for three villages. The training sessions will cover Landfill Equipment Operation and Maintenance, Rural Refrigerant Recovery, and Climate Change Planning for Solid Waste Utilities and Budgeting. In Shaktoolik, direct assistance will reduce black carbon pollution and improve landfill operation safety. In Kongiganak, direct assistance will reduce CFC pollutants and repurpose scrap. In Akiachak, direct assistance will reduce waste pollution and improve landfill operations. This rural development investment will also be used to generate and distribute educational materials on the topics of Fish Net and Tire Recycling and provide one-on-one support to trainees and distressed communities on solid waste, climate change planning, water quality, and backhaul.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to set a realistic water/sewer rate structure for Alaska Rural Utility Collaborative so revenue meet expenses. When rate structures are set too low, system repairs are typically neglected, which decreases the operational life of the water/sewer system. Alaska Rural Utility Collaborative will help deliver dependable, high-quality services to water/sewer customers and assist with disconnecting non-paying customers. The involvement of Alaska Rural Utility Collaborative will also decrease water/sewer operator turnover by providing on-site and off-site training of water treatment plant, distribution, and wastewater operations, and collection and enforcement policy.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Peninsula Solar LLC install a 96 kW photovoltaic (PV) solar array. Peninsula LLC is a newly formed entity created to develop and install various renewable energy projects on the Kenai Peninsula and around the state of Alaska. This project will generate electricity to sell to Fresh365, a locally owned indoor hydroponic farm. The system is estimated to produce 89,700 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year, which is enough electricity to power eight homes.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a regional health center in Seward, Alaska. The health center will serve as a regional hub providing medical, dental, and behavioral health services for Alaskans in rural medically underserved areas. Chugachmiut is a Tribal consortium serving seven Native communities of the Chugach region and seeks to improve health and achieve health equity through access to quality services, a skilled workforce, and innovative programs.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RURAL AK VILLAGES-WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to expand the sewage lagoon in Scammon Bay, Alaska. Construction work for the project will be carried out in concurrence with two closely related, but separately funded, water and sewer construction projects. These three projects will share one set of construction documents and one mobilization and demobilization, which will help decrease project costs overall.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RURAL AK VILLAGES-COMBINATION W&W
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a preliminary engineering and environmental report in Nunam Iqua, Alaska. According to water test results obtained from Drinking Water Watch, the city has challenges meeting disinfection by-product primary contaminant level requirements.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to design and conduct predevelopment activities that will address sewage lagoon berm erosion due to storm and high water events in the community of Kotlik. During high tide events, incoming water washes over effluent. As the tide recedes, it carries water contaminated with effluent through the town and deposits it into the Kotlik River where the raw water intake is located. Erosion causes sewage to leak into the tundra and be in contact with people.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER AND WASTE
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to produce preliminary engineering and environmental reports exploring options for the sewer systems in Russian Mission, Alaska. The sewer mains in the lower part of the community are almost 40 years old and in need of replacement. They are constructed with PVC and copper, and experience repeated leaks and breaks. Several of the deteriorated sewer mains create operational problems, including inability to access manholes to address sewage backups. The lagoons need modifications to obtain permits from the Alaska Department of Environmental Conservation.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a preliminary engineering report for additional water storage in St. Marys, Alaska. The project will include conducting a site visit to evaluate the viability of continuing to use the current two tanks, as well as any needed repairs to the tanks, heat add systems, and yard piping and valving. The report will include a desktop geotechnical review, a desktop Alaska Department of Environmental Conservation contaminated sites review, a cost estimate for the proposed project, and a conceptual layout of the proposed tank, yard piping, and valving.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a pilot study of the water treatment system in Nunam Iqua, Alaska. The study will be conducted during the summer to study the worst possible raw water. The raw water will be tested for contaminants, the treatment system will be reviewed and tested, the treated water will be tested, and then the water will undergo residential reverse osmosis treatment and be tested at its point of use. The studys final report will include recommendations for treatment system upgrades and associated cost estimates.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a preliminary engineering report to address issues with Chignik Lakes water treatment plant and water storage tank.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to prepare preliminary engineering and environmental reports for the water treatment system in Chignik, Alaska. Proposed design, construction, and repairs will stop damage to the water storage tank due to freezing and provide options for removing the cost and risk associated with equipment that is no longer functioning.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Energy 49 LLC install a 6 MW solar system in Houston, Alaska. Energy 49 LLC was created to generate electricity to sell to the Matanuska Electric Association. The system is estimated to produce 9,946,000 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year, which is enough electricity to power 917 homes.

The project consists of 23 one-bedroom units and one three-bedroom unit. All units will undergo significant rehabilitation and improve the living conditions for all current and future tenants.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the City of Shaktoolik develop a preliminary engineering report and an environmental report to evaluate options to replace failing septic tanks and absorption systems.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to increase capacity by providing three solid waste management workshops and conducting 16 environmental assessments of solid waste sites near the Norton Sound on Alaskas western coast. Solid waste managers and operators will have the opportunity to attend the workshops. The environmental assessment will focus on contamination threats to water and air. Leadership and utility managers in Wales, Shishmaref, Gambell, Savoonga, and Shaktoolik will develop sustainable Solid Waste Management Plans.

funding_code: NATIVE AMERICAN TRIBES COMMUNITY FACILITY GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
naics_description: RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IN THE PHYSICAL, ENGINEERING, AND LIFE SCIENCES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to procure equipment for training students to drive a Class B vehicle. The investment will also be used to plan for the construction of a new campus.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RURAL AK VILLAGES-WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve the wastewater treatment system in Kobuk, Alaska. The project will replace two 5,000-gallon septic tanks with two 7,140-gallon septic tanks, install an effluent filter within the final septic tank, excavate the drain field, and dispose of pipe, insulation and unusable material; and construct a drain field. Sludge from the septic tanks will be placed in a one-time use sewage monofil adjacent to the drain field. Other construction waste including removed drain field pipe, insulation, and used septic tanks, will be placed in a one-time use inert waste monofil.

borrower_name: State of Alaska Department of Environmental Conservation
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the City of Buckland develop a technical memo to evaluate options to address reoccurring winter freeze ups in the sewer main from the Buckland Native Store and the sewer lagoon, including consideration of a new lift station.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER AND WASTE
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a preliminary engineering report to address water circulation improvements in Kotzebue, Alaska. The report will explore sewer system improvements and elimination of infiltration and inflow into Lift Station 8.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WATER AND WASTE
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a technical memorandum to support expansion of the sewer system to a new portion of the Kuutchauraq subdivision in Noatak, Alaska. This expansion is needed to connect sewers to new homes. This investment will also be used to develop a preliminary engineering report evaluating alternatives to reinforce or relocate the communitys water source and transmission line and evaluate issues with low water yield at the well.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) RAVG PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANT - WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a preliminary engineering report evaluating the landfill in Shungnak, Alaska, and identifying options to address its deficiencies. Three alternatives will be developed including at least one to close the landfill and construct a new one. The report will assess possible locations for a new site, determine three options that address deficiencies and meet the communitys solid waste needs, and identify a preferred alternative.

funding_code: RURAL UTILITIES SERVICE HIGH ENERGY COST- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to fianc a 200-kW solar PV system and a 500/670 kWh lithium-ion battery energy storage system, related upgrades to the transmission lines and controls to integrate the solar power with the diesel power plant, and energy efficiency upgrades to nine community buildings in the native village of Akiachak, Alaska (population of 627).

funding_code: RURAL UTILITIES SERVICE HIGH ENERGY COST- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace the sub-standard power plant in the village of Napaskiak, Alaska (population 434), with a new power plant that will include heat recovery energy to up to eight end user buildings.

funding_code: RURAL UTILITIES SERVICE HIGH ENERGY COST- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)

funding_code: RURAL UTILITIES SERVICE DENALI COMMISSION- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the community in Minto, which has a population of 170 residents and is located in the Yukon-Koyukuk Census Area. The current pre-PCE cost of electricity is $0.47 per kWh. The community is classified as Distressed by the Alaska Dept of Labor. Their power plant came online in 1971 as a single-phase installation and has been the same for the last 50 years. In 2017 the community in Minto passed a resolution to receive 30 percent of their electrical needs from renewables. In order for this to happen, the electrical system must be upgraded to three-phase. AVEC will install automated switchgear, re-strap the generators, install two new tier rated engines with better fuel efficiency, and upgrade the recovered heat system to include the fire station. Adding the fire station to the heat recovery system will offset approximately 2,400 gallons of diesel fuel. The project will allow the community the opportunity to meet their stated goal of getting 30 percent of their electrical needs from renewables by 2025.

funding_code: COMMUNITY CONNECTIVITY-ORIENTED GTS
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a fiber-to-the-premises (FTTP) system to benefit the 33 residents in the Village of Chenega, Valdez-Cordova Borough, Alaska service area. There will also be improvements to the existing microwave system to expand bandwidth available to support the higher service levels this system will enable. Subscribers will have access to service up of at least 25 Mbps down and 3 Mbps up, expanding access to economic, educational, health care, and public safety opportunities. Computers and free broadband service will provided to residents free of charge for at least two years at the existing community center.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network. AP&T Wireless Inc. will make high-speed internet affordable by its planned participation in the Federal Communications Commissions Lifeline Program and the Affordable Connectivity Program. This project will serve the Klawock and Craig Alaska Native Village Statistical Areas and the socially vulnerable community of Prince of Wales-Hyder.

Project specifics include: demolishing the log crib dam, controlling the release of sediment to the greatest extent possible; constructing a temporary rip-rap access along the crest of the dam to demolish the right abutment, then moving back towards the left abutment remove all the rip-rap and dam in a controlled fashion; constructing a temporary intake below the dam once it is fully removed. naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a health care clinic and provide medical equipment and supplies to deliver primary medical services in Takotna, Alaska. Travel to and from Takotna is conducted via plane on the nearby state-owned 3,300-foot gravel airstrip, and by snow machine, or dogsled during the winter, from McGrath, 17 miles east. funding_code: BUSINESS & INDUSTRY GUARANTEED LOAN - 1%
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This USDA Rural Development investment will be used to provide refinancing for the Waterfall Resort in Ketchikan on Prince of Wales Island, Alaska. The funds will also be used to purchase more fishing vessels for the lodge. This investment will save 150 jobs. In 1911, the Waterfall Cannery was founded on Prince of Wales Islands western shore, because the surrounding waters were known for phenomenal fishing and epic salmon runs. Salmon were caught in fish traps or in nets, brine-cured, packed in handmade cans, and throughout the United States and Europe. Like most Alaska canneries, this frontier outpost was a self-sufficient community of seasonal workers. At each seasons end, most of the crew departed and Waterfall Cannery shut down until the next summers salmon migration. In 1973, the cannery closed permanently, but Waterfall Resorts operating days are still based on the salmon fishing season and the opportunity to fish is a major attraction for resort guests.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to prepare a preliminary engineering report for alternatives to the communitys primary water source in Kasaan, Alaska. Kasaans current water source is an impound with a reinforced concrete dam, a wooden stoplog weir spillway, a concrete intake box and screen, and a steel walkway leading to a steel slide gate on the opposite bank from the access road. An access road extends 550-feet from an old water storage tank to the dam and has one bridge crossing. The access road washes out during the high rain season. The community is seeking an alternative to their existing primary water source to provide more reliable, safer access to water for 49 people.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the Nulato Tribal Council obtain a Preliminary Engineering Report and Environmental Report in Nulato, Alaska. These documents will provide options for extending the water and sewer mains to the Village Public Safety Officers residence, a womens shelter residence, and a multipurpose community building that houses the public works offices. Nulato is located on the west bank of the Yukon River, 35 miles west of Galena and 310 air miles west of Fairbanks. Nulato residents are predominantly Koyukon Athabascans, with a trapping and subsistence lifestyle.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to repair permanent damage to the water distribution system in Koyuk, Alaska. naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to equip two hub/end-user sites and five end-user sites in North Slope Borough, Alaska with equipment required to begin reducing the inequities in provision of telemedicine. Arctic Slope Native Association Ltd. manages Samuel Simmonds Memorial Hospital (SSMH), a critical access hospital in Utqiagvik. Medical professionals working for SSMH will deliver telemedical services focused on chronic and principal care management to patients located at five locations throughout North Slope, benefiting a total of 1,145 residents.
